      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card focuses narrowly on the MD/C-m/C filtering approach, which is one component of the broader PF\u0394Screen workflow. The paper describes a multi-step prioritization process that also includes KMD analysis, diagnostic fragment matching, and suspect screening. The card does not mention these additional prioritization techniques.",
        "The card does not specify that the tool is PF\u0394Screen, only that it uses Python. While Python is correct, the paper's context is specifically about the PF\u0394Screen software tool."
