    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1007_s00216_023_05070_2__task_003/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card focuses narrowly on KMD analysis as a standalone module, but the paper presents KMD as one component of a multi-step prioritization workflow that includes MD/C-m/C filtering, diagnostic fragment matching, and suspect screening. The card does not mention that KMD analysis is typically applied iteratively after MD/C-m/C data reduction to reduce false positives.",
        "The card does not mention that KMD analysis requires user-specified parameters (repeating unit, mass tolerance, minimum number of homologues) and is presented as an interactive, iterative process rather than a standalone automated filter."
      ],
