    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1007_s00216_023_05070_2__task_004/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "After execution, a folder is generated named after the sample file where important results are saved, including a summary in an Excel sheet which is formatted as a table that can be easily inspected, sorted, and subset for a faster overview of the results as well as an additional CSV file that includes the same data (Fig. S2). Important plots are saved in the interactive HTML format which can easily be opened in any browser, allowing zooming and data inspection with interactive tooltips (Fig. S3). In the workflow to prioritize features according to their likelihood of being PFAS, several pieces of evidence are calculated individually for all detected features in the first place... Furthermore, a list of typical PFAS diagnostic fragments (DFs, approximately 900 fragments) from literature are automatically matched with all fragmentation spectra (which is easily extendable) [52, 53].",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes output as Excel/CSV tables with results including diagnostic fragment matches and feature information.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_004",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Feature table or spectrum list with MS2 diagnostic fragment match flags and identified diagnostic masses",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:25:19.259408+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1007_s00216_023_05070_2__task_004/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card focuses narrowly on MS2 diagnostic fragment screening, which is one component of PF\u0394Screen's multi-step workflow. The paper emphasizes that PF\u0394Screen combines multiple prioritization techniques (MD/C-m/C approach, KMD analysis, diagnostic fragments, fragment mass differences, and suspect screening) in an integrated workflow. The card's framing as 'reconstruct the MS2 diagnostic fragment screening filter' is accurate but represents only one module of the broader tool."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 1,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_004",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:25:19.259408+00:00",
