    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/custom-data-schema-mapping/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Only mzML files with centroided spectra and one collision energy (CE) should be used. If profile data was acquired and MS2 spectra from several different CEs per precursor m/z are present, the peak picking (for centroiding) and subset functions (to keep only one desired CE) from MSConvert can be used",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses centroided spectra as a requirement for PF\u0394Screen input.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "custom-data-schema-mapping",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[Python].related_skills",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "centroided-ms-feature-detection",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:28:35.443544+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/custom-data-schema-mapping/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The chemical mass defect (MD) of PFAS is typically lower (MDF = \u2212 0.0016 Da) than the one of hydrocarbons (MDH = + 0.0078 Da) and has been used to remove detected features outside a predefined MD range",
      "asbval:note": "Mass defect calculation is a core technique in PF\u0394Screen's prioritization workflow.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "custom-data-schema-mapping",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[Python].related_skills",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "mass-defect-calculation",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:28:35.443544+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/custom-data-schema-mapping/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Besides the MD and MD/C-m/C approach, the Kendrick mass defect (KMD) analysis to detect homologous series of PFAS (e.g., with CF2 or CF2O as repeating units) is of great relevance",
      "asbval:note": "KMD analysis is explicitly described as a core PF\u0394Screen technique.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "custom-data-schema-mapping",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[Python].related_skills",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "kendrick-mass-defect-calculation",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:28:35.443544+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
