    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/custom-data-schema-mapping/013",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "If feature finding by an external software is desired (e.g., vendor software, alternative open-source tools), the following steps can also be performed by loading a feature table (.csv, that requires m/z, RT, and intensities of the [M] and [M+1] isotopes) into PF\u0394Screen without feature detection via OpenMS. However, the raw mzML files are still needed to assign MS2 data to the features in the feature table",
      "asbval:note": "This is the core functionality described in the task card: mapping external feature lists into PF\u0394Screen's internal representation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "custom-data-schema-mapping",
