      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "data-dependent acquisition (ddMS2) files into the mzML data format... After feature finding in the MS1 data, MS2 spectra can be aligned to their respective precursors by specifying an m/z and RT tolerance. Only one unique MS2 spectrum with the highest precursor intensity is assigned to the respective MS1 precursor.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses data-dependent acquisition (DDA/ddMS2) exclusively and requires precursor-to-fragment alignment. DIA is not discussed; the claim about DIA ambiguity is inferred but not explicitly stated in the paper.",
