    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/md-defect-ratio-calculation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Recently, a promising approach based on the MD normalized to the carbon number (MD/C) vs. the mass normalized to the carbon number (m/C) was proposed to separate PFAS much more efficiently from other hydrocarbon features in HRMS data",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes the MD/C-m/C approach as a core prioritization technique for PFAS identification.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "md-defect-ratio-calculation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Calculate the mass defect (MD) to molecular ion abundance ratio (C-m/C) for each detected feature to identify PFAS-like compounds with elevated mass defects characteristic of perfluorinated structures.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:31:20.354110+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/md-defect-ratio-calculation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Therefore, if the number of features can be preliminarily reduced by the MD/C-m/C approach before applying those techniques, a faster and more accurate NTS workflow can be performed, decreasing both computational and manual effort regarding the further inspection of the features.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms MD/C-m/C is used as an early filtering step to reduce computational burden of downstream analyses.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "md-defect-ratio-calculation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This ratio-based filtering step prioritizes features most likely to be PFAS before more computationally intensive downstream analysis.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:31:20.354110+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/md-defect-ratio-calculation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "PF\u0394Screen can be applied vendor-independently either on mass spectrometric raw data (mzML, automated feature finding via pyOpenMS) or on custom feature lists (external feature finding by other software tools).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly supports both pyOpenMS-detected and custom feature list inputs.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "md-defect-ratio-calculation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have a feature table from LC- or GC-HRMS data (either detected via pyOpenMS or imported as a custom feature list)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:31:20.354110+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/md-defect-ratio-calculation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The PFAS prioritization workflow is intended in an iterative manner: after feature detection, the MD/C-m/C plot should firstly be manually inspected to determine reasonable boundaries to remove most of the detected features (e.g., ~ 90%) that cannot be PFAS due to their MD/C-m/C locations (depending on the underlying question). After determination of these cutoffs, the PFAS feature prioritization can be executed again focused on a subset of features, which will strongly decrease false positives in KMD analysis, fragment matching, and suspect screening",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms MD/C-m/C is applied before KMD analysis and fragment matching.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "md-defect-ratio-calculation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use this as the first prioritization gate to reduce the search space before Kendrick mass defect clustering or MS2 fragment matching.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
