      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The chemical formulas from suspect hits were used to check for reasonable isotope patterns with the RawDataVisualization of PF\u0394Screen... The carbon number can be easily estimated for all HRMS features by using the relative abundance of the M+1 isotope (13C).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes using molecular formulas to validate features and estimate carbon number from isotope patterns before applying PFAS filters.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "molecular-formula-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When to use: When you have a feature list from HRMS with tentatively assigned molecular formulas (from in silico tools or databases) and need to assess formula plausibility before applying downstream PFAS-specific filters.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:31:42.197653+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/molecular-formula-validation/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In the suspect screening process, the hits by accurate mass (tolerance of 4 mDa) were reduced from 217 to 176 by the MD/C-m/C cutoff in soil M1... The verification and (partially manual) identification process of prioritized features from the PF\u0394Screen results table (Excel or CSV) was performed by sorting the table according to decreasing intensity",
      "asbval:note": "The workflow applies MD/C-m/C filtering to reduce suspect hits before manual verification, consistent with the 'when not to use' guidance.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "molecular-formula-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Input is already a curated PFAS suspect list with verified structures \u2014 use this skill for primary screening of unknowns, not re-validation of confirmed identities.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:31:42.197653+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Furthermore, a list of typical PFAS diagnostic fragments (DFs, approximately 900 fragments) from literature are automatically matched with all fragmentation spectra (which is easily extendable) [52, 53]. Both negative and positive fragments are considered depending on the measurement polarity which can be specified in the GUI.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes matching MS2 spectra against a database of ~900 PFAS diagnostic fragments. Fragment mass differences are also calculated and matched.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "A mass spectrometry screening technique that identifies potential PFAS features by matching precursor\u2013product ion pairs in MS2 spectra against a database of known PFAS diagnostic fragments and characteristic mass differences.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:32:01.381027+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For all MS2 spectra, fragment mass differences are calculated comprehensively. Therefore, all fragment differences within each MS2 spectrum are calculated and matched against a predefined list of PFAS typical mass differences (e.g., \u0394CF2, \u0394C2F4, \u0394HF, \u0394C10H3F17, more details can be found in [31]). This allows an efficient detection of fragments indicative for PFAS without prior knowledge on their actual mass [23, 31].",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes flagging features based on PFAS-indicative fragment patterns and mass differences.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This prioritization method flags features whose fragmentation patterns contain diagnostic signatures indicative of PFAS structure.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:32:01.381027+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Feature detection from vendor-independent MS raw data (mzML, data-dependent acquisition) is performed via pyOpenMS (or custom feature lists) with subsequent calculations for prioritization and identification of PFAS in both HPLC- and GC-HRMS data.",
      "asbval:note": "pyOpenMS is explicitly used for processing mzML files and feature detection. The paper also states: 'This task is performed with pyOpenMS, a Python interface to the C++ OpenMS library [42\u201346].' MS2 spectra are aligned to precursors via pyOpenMS.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "pyOpenMS \u2014 Load and parse centroided MS2 spectra from mzML files; extract precursor\u2013product ion pairs for mass matching",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:32:01.381027+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Input MS raw data can be converted vendor-independently from data-dependent acquisition (ddMS2) files into the mzML data format (.mzML) by using the MSConvert software from ProteoWizard [40, 41]. Only mzML files with centroided spectra and one collision energy (CE) should be used.",
      "asbval:note": "MSConvert is explicitly named and described for converting vendor raw data to centroided mzML format.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MSConvert \u2014 Convert vendor-specific raw mass spectrometry data to vendor-independent mzML format with centroided spectra",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:32:01.381027+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We developed PF\u0394 Screen , a Python-based open-source tool with a simple graphical user interface (GUI) to perform efficient feature prioritization using several PFAS-specific techniques such as the highly promising MD/C-m/C approach, Kendrick mass defect analysis, diagnostic fragments (MS 2 ), fragment mass differences (MS 2 ), and suspect screening.",
      "asbval:note": "PF\u0394Screen (case-insensitive match: PF\u0394Screen) is confirmed as the tool implementing MS2 diagnostic fragment matching alongside MD/C-m/C and KMD analysis with a GUI.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "PF\u0394Screen \u2014 End-to-end tool that implements MS2 diagnostic fragment matching as one of three prioritization techniques (alongside MD/C-m/C and KMD analysis) within an integrated GUI workflow",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:32:01.381027+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "PF\u0394Screen is a fully automated tool for detection and prioritization of potential PFAS features (LC- or GC-HRMS with ESI or APCI source) in raw mass spectrometric data written in Python (3.9.13)",
      "asbval:note": "Python 3.9.13 is explicitly stated as the implementation language for PF\u0394Screen.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Python \u2014 PF\u0394Screen is an open-source Python based non-target screening software tool",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:32:01.381027+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Only mzML files with centroided spectra and one collision energy (CE) should be used. If profile data was acquired and MS2 spectra from several different CEs per precursor m/z are present, the peak picking (for centroiding) and subset functions (from MSConvert) can be used to generate the correct mzML input files.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly requires centroided MS2 spectra and describes data-dependent acquisition (ddMS2) workflows.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1007-s00216-023-05070-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ms2-diagnostic-fragment-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have centroided MS2 spectra from data-dependent LC- or GC-HRMS measurements",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:32:01.381027+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
